The [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rand_index Rand index] is a well-known measure of the similarity between two data clusterings. Recently, it has been proposed as a measure of segmentation performance, since a segmentation can be regarded as a clustering of pixels. The [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rand_index Rand index] is defined as a measure of agreement. Here we instead define the closely related Rand error, which is a measure of disagreement.
